<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-25T02:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-25T02:36:00-05:00" n="886" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d886">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12990.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to
                                Mexico to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-25T01:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">August 25, 1914, 1 a.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>133. I conferred with Carranza in the sense of the Department’s August
                            22, 2 p.m., and finally convinced him of the necessity of <pb facs="0707" n="591" xml:id="pg_591"/> dealing with the Diplomatic
                            Corps with due consideration; and, to begin with, he promised to notify
                            the Diplomatic Corps tomorrow of his having taken possession of the
                            Executive Power.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>